detaileddescription.para: Useful for calling upon methods of the base class without knowing it.
Returns: the net owning the rubber.
Returns: one hook (necessarily a master hook) of the ring which has created the rubber.
Returns: the count associated to the rubber (in fact the number of master hooks of the ring).

simplesect.para: This count is at least equal to two else the rubber doesn't exists (no need).

detaileddescription.para: Returns: the center of the rubber (computed at the fly).
Returns: the collection of master hooks that the rubber virtualy connect.

sect1.title: Introduction
sect1.para: Ring introduce the concept of virtual connection between different master hooks present in the ring. Rubber is just introduced to materialize this implicit relation.

sect1.title: Constructors & Destructors
sect1.para: Rubbers are entirely managed by Hurricane. So no constructors nor destructor are avalaible.
